data.title: Does anyone actually enjoy the animated shows by Waco O'Guin and Roger Black (Brickleberry, Paradise PD, Farzar)?

data.text:
Disclaimer: I watched all of them.

So I was wondering if anyone actually thinks those are good shows or they really laugh at such jokes, because most of the jokes and themes feel like you would do in primary school.

The shows all have lots of anal sex jokes, fecal jokes, pedo jokes etc.

I actually wonder how they can continue making shows and got a deal with Netflix for several shows for some years.

They'll all ugly, one-note and bereft of any clever bits so no. They're on the level of Ren & Stimpy's Spike TV run.

Shit and cum aren't worth laughing at because you said "shit" and "cum." There have to be jokes. These turds don't seem to bother with that.

Disclaimer: I watched all of them.

So I was wondering if anyone actually thinks those are good shows or they really laugh at such jokes, because most of the jokes and themes feel like you would do in primary school.

The shows all have lots of anal sex jokes, fecal jokes, pedo jokes etc.

I actually wonder how they can continue making shows and got a deal with Netflix for several shows for some years.

Maybe they're cheap and quick to make? Never seen any of these.

These are kinda a guilty pleasure for me. I low key love them especially while i'm high. I wouldn't recommend to others though as they def are this weird acquired taste.
